longBusinessSummary: Element 29 Resources Inc. acquires, explores for, evaluates, and develops mineral properties in Peru. The company primarily explores for copper, molybdenum, gold, silver, lead, zinc, and other deposits. It owns 100% interests in the Flor de Cobre project comprising seven mining concessions and two concession applications totaling an area of 1,927 hectares located in the Southern Peru; and Elida project that includes 28 mining concessions covering an area of 19,210 hectares located in the province of Ocros. The company also holds interests in the Pahuay Copper Skarn project totaling 700 hectares located to the south of Lima; and MuÃ±aorjo copper project totaling 1,000 hectares in Peru. Element 29 Resources Inc. was incorporated in 2017 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.
